<P>THE INTEREST OF GREAT BRITAIN CONSIDERED With Regard to Her COLONIES AND THE ACQUISITIONS of CANADA and GUADALOUPE.</P>
<P>To which are added, ORSERVATIONS concerning the Increa&s;e of Mankind, Peopling of Countries, <HI>&amp;c.</HI></P>
<P>&rindx;As the very ingenious, u&s;eful, and worthy Author of this Pamphlet [<HI>B&mdash;n F&mdash;n,</HI> LL. D.] is well-known and much e&s;teemed by the principal Gentlemen in <HI>England</HI> and <HI>America;</HI> and &s;eeing that his other Works have been received with univer&s;al Applau&s;e; the pre&s;ent Production needs no further Recommendation to a generous, a free, an intelligent and publick-&s;pirited People.</P>
<P>LONDON, <HI>Printed.</HI> MDCCLX.</P>
<P>BOSTON: <HI>Reprinted, by</HI> B. Mecom, <HI>and Sold at the</HI> New Printing-Office, <HI>near the Town-Hou&s;e.</HI> 1760.</P>
