</LETTER></P></NOTE>; a colony that of all the others receives the lea&s;t addition from &s;trangers. For the increa&s;e of our trade to tho&s;e colonies, I refer to the accounts frequently laid before Parliament, by the officers of the cu&s;toms, and to the cu&s;tom-hou&s;e books: from which I have al&s;o &s;elected one account, that of the trade from <HI>England</HI> (exclu&s;ive of <HI>Scotland</HI>) to <HI>Pen&s;ilvania</HI> <NOTE N="&dagger;" PLACE="foot"><P><HI>An Account of the Value of the Exports from England to Pen&s;yl|vania, in one Year, taken at different Periods,</HI> viz.</P>
